section.def:
client
                (當事人) means any person on whose account a
            solicitor holds or receives client’s money;

paragraph.content:
affect any agreement in writing whenever made between a solicitor and a
                    client of the solicitor as to the application of the client’s money or interest
                    on the money;

subparagraph.content:
money properly required for or towards payment of a debt due to the
                    solicitor from the client or in reimbursement of money expended by the solicitor
                    on behalf of the client;

paragraph.content:
the solicitor in whose name the client account is kept or, where the client
                    account is kept in the name of a firm, any solicitor, partner, consultant or
                    foreign lawyer in the firm;
